summary: I like how this game tried to make Mary Jane more of a proactive character by having her sneak around and gather information,...
body:
I like how this game tried to make Mary Jane more of a proactive character by having her sneak around and gather information, but when she encounters a spider that could potential give her powers, it doesn’t. In fact, not only does the spider not bite her, it hides inside her jacket while she jumps off a building and swings all the way to FEAST. Where it almost immediately bites Miles. 

Having a character be useful without powers is cool and all, but the way that sequence is done is a little ridiculous.

summary: So I'm finally reading Amazing Spider-Girl bc Spider-verse reading made me curious. I'm wowed first off by how charmingly punk...
body:
So I’m finally reading Amazing Spider-Girl bc Spider-verse reading made me curious. I’m wowed first off by how charmingly punk Mayday is, and secondly, by middle-aged!Peter.

He needs to do fisticuffs with a new foe, and he’s thinking of sensibly asking for help when he sees the current generation of perfectly buff and relatively experienced Avengers.

That’s when his brain just hits pause and he has this totally ADULT moment of “Omg. They’re babies. The avengers are babies. I can’t ask them to fIgHT. Omg.” S;lkfjdsl;klkfjsdlkfjdslkfj;dslk

oh, Peter.

blog.description: Stuff I like that I don't think fits in my other blogs!

body:
I’d accept

Spideypool x Vanessa though for sure

Just Wade and Vanessa both being in love with the fluffy little goody-two shoes Petey Parker? YES. They swoon over his rightousness and gush over how adorable he is when he tries to make bad guys stop being bad. Gawd. He’s so cute.

Cuz I like Vanessa. Don’t get me wrong. But if I had to choose between her and Deadpool versus Spideypool I’d definitely choose Spideypool. Hands down. No contest.

BUT I would LIVE for Spideypool x Vanessa for sure.
